        "schemeImageUrl": "",
        "detailedDescription_md": "The &amp;quot;Leave Travelling Concession Scheme&amp;#39;&amp;#39; by the BOCW Welfare Board, Department of Labour, Punjab, is a welfare scheme for the registered workers of the board. Under this scheme, the Board will provide a certain amount as leave travel concession to the registered construction workers for journeys to religious/ historical places in India or visiting their hometown.\n<br>\n\n",
        "benefits_md": "\n  - **Financial Assistance:** An amount of ₹2000/- as Leave Travelling Concession (LTC).\n&gt; **Note:**\n\n\n  - The benefit of L.T.C shall be granted after the return from the journey on submitting Self-declaration/ proof online through the Labour Inspector/Labour Enforcement Officer of the area or through the nearest Suvidha Kendra.\n  - In the event of any incident during the journey, he will not be entitled to any compensation under this scheme.\n\n&lt;br&gt;\n\n",
        "exclusions_md": "Beneficiaries who are getting the benefit of LTC under any similar scheme from any other Govt. Department, will not be entitled for this benefit.\n",
        "briefDescription": "The \"Leave Travelling Concession Scheme'' by the BOCW Welfare Board, Department of Labour, Punjab, is a welfare scheme that provides leave travel concession to the registered construction workers for journeys to religious/ historical places in India or visiting their hometown.\n",
        "detailedDescription": [
